  "text": "It is clear, from the present data, that clonidine, over a range of doses does not affect all aspects of the opioid withdrawal syndrome in rhesus monkeys. Doses were studied that, extrapolating from rodents [CITATION_1] , were likely to affect locus coeruleus activity. Thus, it appears that the withdrawal syndrome is not due entirely to activation of the locus coeruleus.",
